Basic outline:
  function changeTodo() {
		todos[0] = "something new";
	}
	
	this works but it will only change the first todo and you can't specify the new value of that todo
	
	we want to be able to customize 2 things: the number in the brackets for todos (todos[0]) and the item it will equal ("something new")
	
With Parameters:
	function changeTodo(position, new value) {	//this defines 2 new parameters the user can use to choose the position of the todos and what they want the new value to be
		todos[position] = new value;
	}
	
We'll also add a line to display the todos
	function changeTodo(position, new value) {
		todos[position] = new value;
		displayTodos;
	}
